The article is a press gaggle by Principal Deputy Press Secretary Eric Schultz en route to New London, Connecticut. Schultz discusses President Obama's upcoming commencement address at the United States Coast Guard Academy, where he will speak about the importance of acting on climate change and the risks it poses to national security. Schultz also addresses other topics such as vehicle recalls, the fight against ISIS, the oil spill in California, trade with China, Iran's nuclear program, and the Keystone pipeline. He emphasizes the administration's efforts to address climate change and promote clean energy.